<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-11-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-11-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1279" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1279">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/20.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Monterey</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-11-18">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 18, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Referring to my November 17. I have been informed by several Americans
                            that they have been ordered to report to the Governor, to pay several
                            thousand dollars each. On the basis of Department’s instructions to
                            Consular service in Mexico, I shall earnestly protest against Americans
                            being called to pay forced loans.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>